Refactor this O(n^2) duplicate-finder into a single O(n) pass using a hash set:
```py
def dups(xs):
    out = []
    for i, a in enumerate(xs):
        for b in xs[i+1:]:
            if a == b and a not in out:
                out.append(a)
    return out
```

Refactor this BFS to also report the shortest path back to the start node:
```py
def bfs(g, s):
    seen = {s}
    q = [s]
    while q:
        n = q.pop(0)
        for m in g[n]:
            if m not in seen:
                seen.add(m); q.append(m)
    return seen
```
